{
  "texts": [
    "Alternatively, if a tile width is specified in microns, image tiles will be extracted from the nearest higher-magnification pyramid layer and downsized to the target micron width, allowing researchers to granularly specify effective optical magnification.",
    "For this added flexibility, micron-based tile extraction is preferred.",
    "When using cuCIM, images are resized using bilinear interpolation, and when using VIPS, images are resized using Lanczos interpolation [32].",
    "Tile extraction is heavily optimized and multiprocessing accelerated, enabling whole-slide tile extraction at 40x magnification in as little as 2.5 s per slide.",
    "Fast tile extraction enables researchers to quickly experiment with different magnification levels."
  ]
}